md:
giải nghĩa từ "forties" sang tiếng việt; đưa ra nghĩa tiếng việt theo từ loại và đưa ra câu ví dụ, các từ liên quan khác.

* Forties: (plural noun) the period of life between 40 and 49 years old.

Example: "I'm in my forties and I'm feeling more energetic than ever."

* Forties: (noun) the 1940s, a decade in the 20th century.

Example: "The forties were a time of great change and upheaval in the world."

Từ liên quan:

* Thirties: (plural noun) the period of life between 30 and 39 years old.
* Fifties: (plural noun) the period of life between 50 and 59 years old.
* Sixties: (plural noun) the period of life between 60 and 69 years old.
* Seventies: (plural noun) the period of life between 70 and 79 years old.
* Eighties: (plural noun) the period of life between 80 and 89 years old.
* Nineties: (plural noun) the period of life between 90 and 99 years old.

Note: The words "forties", "thirties", "fifties", etc. can also be used to refer to decades in a century, such as the 1940s, 1950s, etc.
